Up for sale is a used HK USP Compact chambered in .40 S&W. It is a variant 7 w/ a bobbed hammer, which means it is DA/SA with a manual safety, and a decocker. I am the second owner. The first owner put around 100 shots through (night stand gun) and I put around 300 or so shots through it. It is one of the older models (pre-2000) but it shoots great (it IS an HK). No box or manual included.

There are two cosmetic discrepancies with the gun. First is there is a slight illegible engraving from the first owner on the slide. It's not hard to miss, but it's not very noticeable unless you are looking for it. The second are dings and scratches on the night sides of the night sights when I (stupidly) installed them with a steel punch. The night sights themselves aren't damaged, and I used a bluing pen to touch them up, but if you look at the sights, you will notice it.

So all together, you will get:
- HK USP Compact .40
- Meprolight Night Sights (installed); unfortunately I don't have the original sights
- Built-To-Fit Leather Holster (no thumb strap, open bottom)

title: For Sale:  Anti-Car Ambush/Jacking Seminar next Sunday in Miami
postcontent:
What: Anti-Vehicular Ambush / Anti-Car Jacking Seminar
When: May 31st - 12:30 PM
Where: Miami Shooters Club location
Contact Number: REDACTED
Website: website www.MiamiShootersClub.com


Next Sunday, May 31st, 12:30pm, we will be teaching an anti-vehicular ambush / anti-car jacking seminar in Miami.  We will meet at the Miami Shooters Club location to practice in the parking lot with rubber guns - and then we'll drive out to a special private range and practice with live ammunition inside and around an actual car.  

To practice with live ammunition, a basic shooting pre-qualification test will be done first, and if you pass, we'll practice with real ammo.  If you fail, no problem, it just means you need more practice, but for safety reasons we'll do the drills with simunitions, which works just like real ammunition except that it shoots a paint bullet.  Simunitions use real guns and are fired with a powder charge like a real gun (not like airsoft) so for the purposes of training, it will be more than sufficient for beginner shooters.

ZERO experience is required - a basic firearms class will be taught for beginners as well.  You do NOT need to own a firearm, we can provide one at no charge.

The seminar will be 4 hours long and the price is $297 for one person.  Since we really encourage spouses to train together, or close friends to train together, the price for two or more people coming together is only $197 each - that's $100 off each person.  Miami Shooters Club members get an additional 10% OFF.  We will also provide firearms if needed at no charge and there is no range fee - however, ammunition is not included.  We do sell ammunition and simunition ammo.  If you're a beginner and would prefer to shoot with simunitions rather than real ammo, that is fine.

Certified NRA instructors Kevin Perez, Victoria Fernandez, Devin Genchi, and myself will be teaching the seminar. The techniques from this particular seminar we learned from two separate ten-day-long trips to Asymmetric Solutions where we got to train under former CIA and military such as Green Berets and Navy Seals.  Now we are bringing the knowledge to our students in Miami.  The video above features Kevin Perez and I at Asymmetric Solutions.

We will have a single vehicle to shoot from - for that reason, we have to limit the class size to eight people.  The first eight people to register will get to participate - first-come, first serve.

If you would like to reserve a spot at the seminar, please call us at REDACTED. 

At the seminar, we'll also share more info about our weekly firearms self defense class that we've been conducting at Miami Shooters Club which includes, but is not limited to:

Firearm Safety 
Pistol 
Rifle 
Shotgun 
Protection Inside the Home (versus home invasion) 
Protection Outside the Home (concealed carry) 
Protection from Inside Your Car 
Close Quarter Combat (with pistol and rifle) 
Gun and Knife Disarms 

We conduct one weekly class at Miami Shooters Club (MSC) and one live fire day at a private tactical range that we have reserved for the first Sunday of every month. We practice at MSC throughout the week and go live, safely, at the range. Live fire is optional but recommended. 

Here is a sample of the sort of training we will practice next Sunday: https://youtu.be/4oTHGxFtFc8

We are also planning another group trip to Asymmetric Solutions to train at their new Jacksonville facility opening up this fall - if you are interested in that too, just let us know.  We have a special relationship with Asymmetric Solutions and get phenomenal discounts. 

Call us at REDACTED or visit our website www.MiamiShootersClub.com if you would like to check out our seminar and/or our weekly gun class at our facility.  You do NOT need a gun to attend (we have loaners at no cost).  The class covers a lot of theory and practical application.  We cover how to use revolvers, semi-auto pistols, shotguns, rifles, and more.

title: For Sale:  Don't pay these High Prices, find real deals easily
postcontent:
Do a little research and don't pay an extra $100+ for guns listed on here that aren't even new.  Check out a few websites and with one easy search you can find really cheap deals and have them shipped to a local FFL in your area.  Then you are supporting a local FFL business, buying a brand new firearm and saving a bunch of money.  
SlickGuns.com
GunWatcher.com
WikiArms.com
These are 3 easy websites to check out pricing of NUMEROUS retailers.  

Taurus PT111 G2 can be had for about $199-$225 shipped.  Don't be a fool and over pay for something, ESPECIALLY USED, when you can buy BRAND NEW with WARRANTY for less $$$$.  

Keep prices down for every one by buying smart and looking around... all 2nd Amendment supporters will appreciate it.

title: For Sale:  Hungarian SA85M FEG post-ban KBI import 7.62x39 akm (ak-47 variant)
postcontent:
Its been said the Hungarians put out one of the finest, non-milled AK variant rifles with its SA85M. I bought the rifle in its post '89 ban "sporterized" condition; that means thumbhole stock, no threaded barrel,  no bayonet lug and a chopped gas block ( no way to properly secure a cleaning rod). Rifle has been restored to pre-ban status (minus the blonde wood and gloss black finish) and legally, per Title 18 U.S.C 922r. 

Factory 16" barrel has been threaded to M14x1LH 
Rear gas block pressed off and swapped for a uncut Romanian gas block (closest match to Hungarian part).
Front sight block pressed off and swapped to a uncut Hungarian front with lug and detent.
Hungarian fire control group swapped for Tapco G2 Single hook group (922r 3 parts).
Old wood furniture swapped for custom IronWood Designs African Teak (922r 3 parts). Finished in Waterlox Tung Oil.
Cerakoted Graphite Black.
Cnc Warrior slant brake.
Hungarian cleaning kit in stock
Cleaning rod off AMD-65
Hungarian leather sling.

I also added a 2" picatinny rail and 6" riser rail (removeable) under the foregrip to accomodate a bipod for hunting; took the idea from a Dragunov; didn't want to drill into the wood.

This particular rifle left FEG with a Hungargian AMD-65 short piston and short gas tube. The majority recevied the longer, more common tube and piston. 

If you know your AKs, you'll appreciate this. Make me an offer. If I don't respond, its either sold  or your offer was not reasonable.

title: For Trade:  73 (Pre Lock) S&W 10-5 Rarer 2" Round Butt + Extras
postcontent: In excellent condition and has very few rounds through it. Blued with color case hardened action and wearing Pachmayr Gripper Grips. Fires and fuctions flawlessly. Still as tight as new. Except for the grips its all orginal. Traditional DA/SA six round medium sized "snub nose". Production date of 1973. Has all the features of a classic S&W revolver like a pinned barrel, hammer mounted firing pin, pre MIM parts and of course its pre lock. The 2" barrel paired to the round butt frame is one of the desirable less common pairings most are on a square butt frame. Was rated in its day for beyond the modern equivalent of +P. Comes with a HKS speed loader and a 40rd box of Remington SJHP. Makes a great addtion if your a collector or it still makes a perfect EDC option. Only trading because I have a couple other medium size 38s I have more of a sentimental attachment to and want something else. Would prefer to trade but might sell. Transfer on EFA10 or at a FFL. Must have a Mass LTC and follow all laws.

title: For Sale:  G36 Tactical .22 Conversion-Highly Upgraded
postcontent:
This is a one of a kind set up and shoots reliably and very accurate at 2-3 inch groups our to 100 yards. 

The rifle started out as a $300 Mossberg 715T AR-15 style .22 semi-auto.  I didn't like the look and feel of the upper and lower, so I removed the barrel, trigger group (these are integrated as a single unit, but can be disassembled for cleaning) and I added a $200 Archangel Marauder G36 Kit (the one designed for the Ruger 10/22) and fabricated the setup to marry to the Mossberg barrel and internals.

There isn't another G36 variant out there chambered in .22 that looks this cool.  It gets a lot of attention at the range.

I've got several other .22 rifles and now that I completed this project, I'm moving on to the next one.

Offering this at a very good deal considering all the upgrades and work.
